<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>materialize-monitoring Operations on materialize-monitoring Documentation</title><link>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/</link><description>Recent content in materialize-monitoring Operations on materialize-monitoring Documentation</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Production Best Practices</title><link>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/production-best-practices/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/production-best-practices/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="production-best-practices"&gt;Production Best Practices&lt;a class="anchor" href="#production-best-practices"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Production guidance for the &lt;code&gt;materialize-monitoring&lt;/code&gt; stack, organized by backend.
Every checklist item is tagged with its &lt;strong&gt;primary owner&lt;/strong&gt; under the &lt;a href="#shared-responsibility-model"&gt;shared responsibility model&lt;/a&gt;, and is checked (&lt;code&gt;[x]&lt;/code&gt;) when the chart already ships it as a default — unchecked items are the deployment-time actions (or still-to-build chart work) that remain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today this covers the &lt;strong&gt;collection tier (Alloy)&lt;/strong&gt; and the bundled &lt;strong&gt;logging backend (Loki)&lt;/strong&gt;; metrics (Thanos), Grafana, and Alertmanager sections will follow the same shape.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>o11y Troubleshooting</title><link>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/o11y-troubleshooting/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/o11y-troubleshooting/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="o11y-troubleshooting"&gt;o11y Troubleshooting&lt;a class="anchor" href="#o11y-troubleshooting"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</description></item><item><title>Meta Observability</title><link>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/meta-observability/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/meta-observability/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="meta-observability"&gt;Meta Observability&lt;a class="anchor" href="#meta-observability"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</description></item><item><title>Upgrading materialize-monitoring</title><link>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/upgrading/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/upgrading/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="upgrading-materialize-monitoring"&gt;Upgrading materialize-monitoring&lt;a class="anchor" href="#upgrading-materialize-monitoring"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="ingester-rollouts-duration-and-deploy-timeouts"&gt;Ingester rollouts: duration and deploy timeouts&lt;a class="anchor" href="#ingester-rollouts-duration-and-deploy-timeouts"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any change to the ingester pod spec — image, resources, or scaling the replica count — rolls the ingester StatefulSet.
That roll is &lt;strong&gt;ordered and readiness-gated&lt;/strong&gt;: pods cycle &lt;strong&gt;one at a time&lt;/strong&gt;, and the next is not touched until the previous re-joins the ring and reports Ready.
This is deliberate — with &lt;code&gt;replication_factor: 3&lt;/code&gt;, one-at-a-time keeps at most one of three replicas down, preserving write quorum throughout the roll.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Securing</title><link>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/securing/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/securing/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="securing-materialize-monitoring"&gt;Securing materialize-monitoring&lt;a class="anchor" href="#securing-materialize-monitoring"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</description></item><item><title>Tuning</title><link>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/tuning/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://materializeinc.github.io/materialize-monitoring/preview/version-update-mzmon-lib/operating/tuning/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="tuning-your-observability-stack"&gt;Tuning your Observability Stack&lt;a class="anchor" href="#tuning-your-observability-stack"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>